body:
**Description**

Just wondering if this is a bug, but when I load a PNG and explicitly request the bitmap to have alpha = opaque, nothing gets drawn on the canvas. (However a jpg of the same image works fine?). The call to GetPixels also seems to end far too quickly as if it's not even reading anything from the file.

**Code**

```
            var codec = SKCodec.Create("myimage.png");

            var codecInfo = codec.Info;
            SKImageInfo desiredInfo = new SKImageInfo(codecInfo.Width, codecInfo.Height);
            desiredInfo.AlphaType = SKAlphaType.Opaque;

            bitmap = new SKBitmap(desiredInfo);
            codec.GetPixels(bitmap.Info, bitmap.GetPixels());
```

**Expected Behavior**

A bitmap with no transparency.

**Actual Behavior**

No pixels loaded?

**Basic Information**

- Version with issue:  2.80.3-pre-90, 2.80.2
- IDE:  VS 2019
- Platform Target Frameworks: <!-- all that apply, remove the platforms that aren't broken or haven't had any testing -->
  - Windows Classic:  Windows 10 using WinForms with SkiaSharp.Views.Desktop.SKGLControl
